Pick a couple,

00:01:04.670 --> 00:01:09.420
then use some of the techniques you have learned in lesson two to analyze them.

00:01:09.420 --> 00:01:13.330
For example, you could calculate the information gain both for

00:01:13.330 --> 00:01:18.830
the Euclidean distance we chose earlier and the Manhattan distance denoted here.

